09/12/2002
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Simitis announced he would continue his European tour Monday (9 December) in view of the EU summit in Copenhagen, which starts Thursday. Greece will be presiding over the EU for the first six months of 2003. Simitis met with his Italian counterpart Silvio Berlusconi on Saturday. He meets Monday in Madrid with Spain's Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar.
In other news, the Greek government declared a state of emergency in the north and in central areas of the country after strong storms caused rivers to burst their banks. Rising waters and mudslides cut off a key highway between Athens and Thessaloniki on Sunday, trapping motorists. The railroad line linking Greece's two largest cities was also flooded. (Macedonian Press Agency, Athens News Agency, AFP - 08/12/02)
